%livy2.spark

import scala.io.Source
import org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configuration;
import org.apache.hadoop.fs.FileSystem;
import org.apache.hadoop.fs.Path;
import java.io.PrintWriter;


val path = "/user/tg1/landing/datasets/timely.csv"
val time = spark.read.option("header","true").csv(path)  // Create a DataFrame from JSON data (automatically infer schema and data types)


val data_time = time.drop("Facility ID", "Address", "ZIP Code", "County Name", "Phone Number", "Measure Name", "Footnote")

val dt2 = data_time.withColumnRenamed("Facility Name","Facility_Name").withColumnRenamed("Measure ID","Measure_ID").withColumnRenamed("Start Date","Start_Date").withColumnRenamed("End Date","End_Date")
    
val dt3 = dt2.withColumn(
    "Score",
    when(
        $"Score".equalTo("Not Available") || $"Score".equalTo(" "),
        null
        ).otherwise($"Score")).withColumn(
    "Sample",
    when(
        $"Sample".equalTo("Not Available") || $"Sample".equalTo(" "),
        null
        ).otherwise($"Sample")).withColumn(
    "Score",
    when(
        $"Score".equalTo("high") || $"Score".equalTo("High"), 
        150
        ).otherwise($"Score")).withColumn(
    "Score",
    when(
        $"Score".equalTo("medium") || $"Score".equalTo("Medium"),
        90
        ).otherwise($"Score")).withColumn(
    "Score",
    when(
        $"Score".equalTo("low") || $"Score".equalTo("Low"), 
        10
        ).otherwise($"Score"))withColumn(
    "Score",
    when(
        $"Score".equalTo("very high"), 
        300
        ).otherwise($"Score"))
        
val dt4 = dt3.na.drop()


dt4.count()
dt4.printSchema()
dt4.show(200)

def expr(myCols: Set[String], allCols: Set[String]) = {

    case x if myCols.contains(x) => col(x)
    case _ => lit(null).as(x)
